@node hayes "Index"
@toc index

    Index - Hayes Command Set


        +++     escape code
        AT      attention code
        A       answer phone line
        A/      repeat last command
                    not preceeded by AT command
                    not followed by a carriage return
        B       CCIT V.21/V.22 protocols
        B1      Bell 103/212A protocols
        Dxą     dial the following number; ie ATD 555-1414
        Ex      echo commands
                    0 = disable
                    1 = enable
        Hx      hook control
                    0 = on hook or hang up
                    1 = off hook
        Ix      return product ID, or return checksum
        Lx      speaker volume
                    [ 0, 1, 2, 3, ...]
                    0 = low
        M       speaker OFF
        M1      speaker ON until carrier received
        M2      speaker always on
        M3      speaker disabled while dialing and after carrier
        N       connect only at speed in register S37
                    0 = last AT command issued
        N1      connect at highest possible speed
        O       return online
        O1      return online with retrain
        P       set pulse dial as default
        Qx      result codes
                    0 = enabled
                    1 = disabled
                    2 = enabled while originating; disabled when answering
        Sr      return value stored in register r
        Sr=x    set register r to a value of x
        T       set tone dial as default
        V       result codes
                    0 = numeric
                    1 = verbose
        Wx      error correction call progress
                    0 = not reported; CONNECT reports DTE speed
                    1 = reported
                    2 = not reported; CONNECT reports DCE speed
        X       blind dial; ignore dial tone and busy signal; send CONNECT
        X1      blind dial; do not detect busy signal; send CONNECT
        X2      wait for dial tone; do not detect busy signal; send CONNECT
        X3      ignore dial tone; send BUSY if detected; send CONNECT
        X4      wait for dial tone; send BUSY/NO DIALTONE if detected, send CONNECT
        Y       long space disconnect
                    0 = disabled
                    1 = enabled
        Zx      reset modem and load stored configuration x


        &C      DCD signal always on
        &C1     DCD ON indicates data carrier from remote modem
        &D      ignore DTR signal
        &D1     switch to asynchronous upon ON to OFF DTR transition
        &D2     disconnect
        &D3     perform soft reset upon ON to OFF DTR transition
        &Fx     load factory default configuration [0..255]
        &Jn     telephone wall jack type
                    1 = RJ-11/RJ-41/RJ-45S standard line
        &K      disable flow control
        &K3     enable bidirectional hardware flow control (RTS/CTS)
        &K4     enable software flow control (XON/XOFF)
        &K5     enable transparent software flow control (XON/XOFF)
        &Lx     line selection
                    0 = dial up
        &Mx     same as &Q
        &Px     pulse dial make/break ratio
                    0 = 39/61 10pps
                    1 = 33/67 10pps
                    2 = 33/67 20pps
        &Q      mode selection
                    0 = direct async
                    1 = sync1
                    2 = sync2
                    3 = sync3
                    5 = error correcting async
                    6 = normal async
        &Rx     RTS/CTS sync mode
                    0 = CTS responds to RTS
                    1 = CTS on
        &Sx     select DSR action
                    0 = always on
                    1 = EIA recommendation
        &Tx     test modem [0..8]
        &V      show configurations
        &Wx     write active configuration to nonvolatile memory
        &Xx     synchronous transmit clock source
                    0 = internal
                    1 = external
                    2 = slave receive
        &Yx     load stored configuration profile at power-up [0..255]
        &Zx=n   store phone number n in address x [0..255]


        \Ax     MNP maximum block size
                    0 = 64
                    1 = 128
                    2 = 192
                    3 = 256
        \Bx     transmit break [1..255]
        \Gx     modem to modem flow control
                    0 = disabled
                    1 = XON/XOFF
        \Kx     break processing [0..255]
        \Lx     MNP link
                    0 = stream
                    1 = block
        \Nx     operating mode
                    0 = normal
                    1 = direct
                    2 = MNP reliable
                    3 = autoreliable
                    4 = LAPM/MNP reliable
        \O      originate MNP reliable link
        \Tx     set inactivity timer
                    0 = disabled
                    [1..255] = minutes
        \U      accept MNP reliable link
        \Y      establish MNP reliable link
        \Z      switch from MNP to normal mode


        %Cx     data compression
                    0 = disabled
                    1 = enabled
        %Dx     set BLTZ dictionary size
                    0 = 512
                    1 = 1024
                    2 = 2048
                    3 = 4096
        %Ex     auto retrain
                    0 = disabled
                    1 = enabled
        %L      report received signal level (-dBm)
        %M      BLTZ compression
                    0 = disabled
                    1 = transmit only
                    2 = receive only
                    3 = receive and transmit
        %P      reset local and remote modem's BLTZ dictionaries
        %Q      report line signal quality [0..8]
                    0 = good
                    8 = poor
        %Sx     set maximum BLTZ string length [6..250]


        -B      fall back to 1200 BPS at -10 dBm
        -K      don't convert LAPM connection
        -K1     convert LAPM to MNP 10 connection
        -Ux     change to transmit level during fall forward [0..7]


        *H      negotiate link at highest supported rate
        *H1     negotiate link at 1200 BPS


        )Mx     try to reduce power level to less than -10 dBm

            xą represents a value [0..255]

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node hayes.s "Index"
@toc index

    Index - Hayes S Registers


            Register values and uses may vary.

          S0    ring to answer on                       [0..255]
          S1    ring count                              [0..255]
          S2    escape code                             [0..255]
          S3    carriage return code                    [0..127]
          S4    line feed character                     [0..127]
          S5    back space character                    [0..32]
          S6    wait to blind dial                      [0..255]ą
          S7    to wait for data carrier                [1..255]ą
          S8    comma pause time                        [0..255]ą
          S9    carrier detect response time            [1..255]˛
         S10    delay from lost carrier to hangup       [1..255]˛
         S11    DTMF tone duration                     [50..255]˛
         S12    escape code guard time                  [0..255]˛
         S16    diagnostic test options
         S18    test timer                              [0..255]ą
         S25    delay to DTR change                     [0..255]˛
         S26    RTS to CTS delay                        [0..255]˛
         S30    inactivity timer                        [0..255]ł
         S36    negotiation failure treatment           [0..7]
         S37    desired DCE line speed                  [0..6]
         S38    delay before forced disconnect          [0..255]
         S40    MNP options
         S41    MNP options
         S46    compression selection
         S48    V.42 negotiation
         S82    break handling
         S86    connection failure cause code
         S91    programmable transmit level

            ą measured in seconds
            ˛ measured in split seconds
            ł ten second intervals

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


